Estimated time to recovery : 1 hour(s)

Affected instances

The list of instances listed below are currently unavailable, due to hardware fault on the hypervisor(s) previously mentioned. We apologize for any inconvenience caused while we resolve this issue.

Start time : 18/12/2022 10:12 UTC Service impact : Cooling system performance may for lowered the time being. Ongoing actions : Investigating Our technical teams are working on the issue. Update will be post as significant progress is made.
The fix has been postponed for next Monday 19/12/2022.
The fix will be implemented tomorrow 16/12/2022 during the day.

Start time : 15/12/2022 15:09 UTC  Service impact : Customers that would like to add a floating IP to their network will take more time then usual to be implemented Ongoing actions : Our teams have identified the cause of the incident and are currently preparing a fix
Maintenance will begin as scheduled in 60 minutes.

Start time : 19/12/2022 09:00 UTC  End time : 19/12/2022 10:45 UTC Service impact : None Service improvement : The objective of this maintenance is to remove options 'rescue64-pro' and 'rescue64-ovh' and replace them by 'rescue-customer' in 'Boot rescue mode' for dedicated and virtual private servers. To use rescue mode, you can refer to the current link: https://docs.ovh.com/fr/dedicated/ovh-rescue/#en-pratique
